More than 2,000 traders in Ngong have been relocated to a temporary market to pave way for construction of a 700million shilling ultra?modern market after months of an unending standoff. The new three acres temporary market located at Ngong stadium was opened officially by transport and infrastructure CS James Macharia promising traders booming business. Â The 180m shilling temporary market has a capacity to accommodate more than 2000 traders with each trader allocated a four by four feet operation space.